From f3a676c278711de64f26603fe12ce282571ce36b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: TBFS Security Review <review@tbfs.local>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 11:09:30 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 01/10] F-01/F-14/F-15: ignore client PII; deploy allowlisted
 app shell only

- Add Loans/ (client PII) and dist/ to .gitignore. Untracking the
  already-committed Loans/ files and desktop.ini, plus the history
  purge, are one-time commands in the apply guide (kept out of this
  patch so it applies cleanly before or after the git-filter-repo run).
- deploy.yml now builds dist/ via tools/build-dist.sh (explicit runtime
  allowlist) so GitHub Pages can never serve internal docs, client PDFs,
  or dev/test pages (F-14).
- Add tools/check-html-scripts.mjs, the inline-script syntax gate used
  throughout this patch series.
